title: Watch: Ducks game highlights as Vernon Adams Jr. passes for two TDs in win at Washington
text:
Vernon Adams Jr. got the start at quarterback and led the Oregon Ducks to a 26-20 win against the Washington Huskies in Seattle on Saturday.
He completed 14 of 25 passes for 272 yards and two touchdowns and looked sharp for most of the game, after being limited by a broken finger most of the season.
Royce Freeman chipped in 138 yards on 27 carries and Darren Carrington caught both touchdown passes and finished with five receptions for 125 yards.
Huskies quarterback Jake Browning threw for 199 yards and a touchdown and Myles Gaskin rushed for 155 yards, including a 72-yard touchdown run in the third quarter that got Washington to within 10 points, 23-13.
Washington cut the lead to 26-20 late in the fourth quarter and had the ball in the final minute of the game before Oregon's Ugo Amadi 's intercepetion sealed the win.
With the win, Oregon improves to 4-3 (2-2 Pac-12).
